  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Manager",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><p><strong>Sales & Business Development</strong></p><ul><li>Identify, develop, and manage new business opportunities within the Singapore market for digital and IT solutions.</li><li>Perform prospecting through cold calls, digital outreach, networking events, and industry platforms.</li><li>Understand customer requirements and recommend suitable IT solutions (e.g., cloud, SaaS, cybersecurity, infrastructure, digital platforms).</li><li>Prepare and deliver sales proposals and presentations.</li><li>Manage the full sales cycle from lead generation to closing deals.</li><li><strong>Client Management</strong></li><li>Build strong relationships with new and existing clients to ensure long-term partnerships.              Provide consultative guidance to help clients optimise their IT and digital transformation strategies.Work closely with technical teams to ensure smooth implementation and post‑sales support.</li><li><strong>Sales Operations</strong></li><li><p>Track sales pipeline and forecast revenue.<br />Meet and exceed monthly and quarterly sales targets.<br />Monitor market trends, competitors, and customer needs to enhance sales pipeline.</p></li><li>Degree in Business, Information Technology, or related fields.</li><li>Min 3- 5 years of experience in IT sales, digital solutions sales, SaaS sales, or related fields.</li><li>Strong understanding of IT products and digital technologies (cloud, cybersecurity, software, digital platforms).</li><li>Excellent communication, presentation, and negotiation skills.</li><li>Sales-driven, goal‑oriented, and proactive in acquiring new business.</li><li>Ability to translate technical information into business benefits.</li></ul>",
